    <item>
      <title>What if we paid doctors to keep people healthy - TedTalk 2017</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/what-if-we-paid-doctors-to-keep-people-healthy-tedtalk-2017/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 23 Aug 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/what-if-we-paid-doctors-to-keep-people-healthy-tedtalk-2017/</guid>
      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#video&#34;&gt;Video&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#transcript&#34;&gt;Transcript&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#other-items-on-the-topic&#34;&gt;Other items on the topic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;video&#34;&gt;Video&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ted.com/talks/matthias_mullenbeck_what_if_we_paid_doctors_to_keep_people_healthy/transcript?user_email_address=e37d32694f4c44a5bda4fa26573c9726&amp;amp;lctg=62d1bd0354733608146b37e8&#34;&gt;TedTalk 10:30&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matthias Müllenbeck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As the Biopharma director for licensing and business development at Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany, Matthias Müllenbeck is responsible for leading strategic partnering initiatives in the field of oncology and immuno-oncology.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;transcript&#34;&gt;Transcript&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;00:00&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s 4am in the morning. I&amp;rsquo;m waking up in a Boston hotel room and can only think of one thing: tooth pain. One of my ceramic inlays fell off the evening before. Five hours later, I&amp;rsquo;m sitting in a dentist&amp;rsquo;s chair. But instead of having a repair of my inlay so that I can get rid of my pain, the dentist pitches me on the advantages of a titanium implant surgery. Ever heard of that?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Off Topic: DNA data finally being used to identify diseases caused by genes</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/off-topic-dna-data-finally-being-used-to-identify-diseases-caused-by-genes/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/off-topic-dna-data-finally-being-used-to-identify-diseases-caused-by-genes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;nav id=&#34;TableOfContents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;ul&gt;&#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#new-ai-tool-searches-genetic-haystacks-to-find-disease-causing-variants&#34;&gt;New AI tool searches genetic haystacks to find disease-causing variants&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;          &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/li&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/nav&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;new-ai-tool-searches-genetic-haystacks-to-find-disease-causing-variants&#34;&gt;New AI tool searches genetic haystacks to find disease-causing variants&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.washingtonpost.com/science/2023/06/01/primate-ai-genome-variants/?utm_campaign=wp_the_optimist&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;utm_source=newsletter&amp;amp;wpisrc=nl_optimist&amp;amp;carta-url=https%3A%2F%2Fs2.washingtonpost.com%2Fcar-ln-tr%2F3a2e1f3%2F647c8b64e49da13a6d45e983%2F596bdb5f9bbc0f403f990f33%2F28%2F44%2F647c8b64e49da13a6d45e983&#34;&gt;Washington Post $$&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;The scientists built the algorithm, called PrimateAI-3D, using the genetic blueprints of 233 different primate species. This base brings into sharp relief the variants that can be tolerated by primates, including humans, and those that prove deadly. Scientists look for places where the sequence is the same from one primate to another, a clear sign that any change is disastrous.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Off topic: back muscle pain quickly treated by TENS</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/off-topic-back-muscle-pain-quickly-treated-by-tens/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/off-topic-back-muscle-pain-quickly-treated-by-tens/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A few times a year a tiny portion of my back would seize up making movement and walking  painful&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In April 2022 I purchased a  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00NCRE4GO/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&amp;amp;psc=1&#34;&gt;$32 TENS machine from Amazon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/attachments/d3.mock.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;image&#34; width=&#34;400&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The next opportunity to use the TENS machine was in Jan 2023&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Pain is almost entirely gone after ~ four 30-minute treatments in a single day&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It has lots of options - but I only used the defaults on level 3 intensity out of 10&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
